Estonian at primary school has the biggest number of lessons and links all the other subjects. It is is important for the development of children and gives all the necessary skills for life, such as listening, speaking, reading and writing. Developing each language skill requires different knowledge from a teacher.Teaching writing at primary school includes teaching calligraphy, ortography and creative writing. All these require different techniques. The course deals with various aspects of teaching Estonian at primary school.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge and skills to work as a teacher of Estonian at primary school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student can design a syllabus based on it; can design a lesson plan for the Estonian language class, considering the skills and abilities of children, incl. special educational needs; can direct the learning process and will know different methods for teaching Estonian at primary school; can monitor and identify children's progress and evaluate the efficiency of teaching; will set a role model for pupils and teach them values.
